HEADWORD: Straight-out
<hw>Straight"-out`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Acting without
concealment, obliquity, or compromise; hence, unqualified;
thoroughgoing.</def> <mark>[Colloq. U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Straight-out</qex> and generous indignation.</q>
<rj><qau>Mrs. Stowe.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Straight-pight</ent>⟦br⟧
